<HEAD>Slain Teen-ager Remembered In Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEASIDE, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 15-year-old girl whose disappearance in mid-June led to a search by hundreds of volunteers, was remembered at her memorial service Sunday as a precious child. Mourners filled the main hall of the Seaside Civic and Convention Center for services honoring slaying victim <PERSON> Dorene </PERSON> <PERSON> Raterman </PERSON> of <PERSON> Gearhart </PERSON>. In a prayer to God, the Rev. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Seaside </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Baptist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> said, `` We need to hear from you. We need to feel your great arm of love and strength right now.'' `` You're the only one who can make sense right now out of this loss and hurt,'' he said. The teen-ager vanished June 15 after leaving her parents a note saying she was taking a bicycle ride to a beach half a mile from her home. Her remains were found July 25 in a brushy area about 16 miles east of <LOCATION> Astoria </LOCATION>, on the state's northwest coast. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Mullins </PERSON>, 20, was charged with murder and kidnapping, and <ORGANIZATION> Tiac </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION>, 25, was charged with hindering prosecution. <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> told the memorial gathering of more than 1,000 people that <PERSON> Doreen </PERSON> was a `` precious child.'' `` Happy, friendly, loving, a joy to her parents, a blessing from God. She was Daddy's little girl.''
