on. The information was used successfully in trials of suspected Mafia drug traffickers. <PERSON> Falcone </PERSON> won the cooperation of <PERSON> Tomasso </PERSON> <PERSON> Buscetta </PERSON>, a Mafia leader who broke the mob's code of silence to describe its command structure in the 1987 trial. <PERSON> Falcone </PERSON> has become a national symbol of <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s war on organized crime and is considered its top investigator of the Mafia.
